modules.description: Provides constant-time string equality checking and related operations to prevent timing attacks. Works with strings and byte sequences, ensuring execution time remains independent of input values. Used to securely compare sensitive data like passwords or cryptographic keys.

Compares Cstruct.t values for equality and lexicographical order in both big-endian and little-endian formats, with optional length constraints. Identifies the first occurrence of a byte matching a predicate or checks if any byte satisfies a condition, starting from a specified offset. Designed for low-level binary data inspection and comparison in network or file protocols.
